Add more visuals to make this product more visually pleasing 
To add more visuals to your habit tracking RPG site and make it more visually pleasing, you could try the following:

Add a background image or color: A background image or color can help to give your site a more cohesive look and feel. You can use a patterned image or a solid color for the background, depending on the style you want to achieve.

Use icons or graphics: Icons or graphics can be a great way to add visual interest to your site. For example, you could use icons to represent the different habit types (e.g. a leaf icon for good habits and a fire icon for bad habits).

Use responsive design: Responsive design ensures that your site looks good on a variety of device sizes. Consider using a responsive layout and designing your site with different device sizes in mind.

Use whitespace: Whitespace is the empty space around elements on your site. It can help to make your site look more visually appealing and easier to read.

Use typography effectively: Typography is the use of fonts and text on your site. You can use different font sizes, weights, and styles to create hierarchy and draw attention to important elements on your site.

I hope these suggestions are helpful! Let me know if you have any questions or need further assistance.




